Hey guys, I am new here and not a dev but I am building a platform I wish to run on a decentralized server...Is it possible to move our current AWS stack onto SN27 to make it completely decentralized? or am I off the mark here? 

How does it work in terms of running an AWS stack on SN27 

Thank you in advance!

SN27 currently allows validators to reserve docker containers on miner machines. We’re finishing some final testing before the full rollout of this functionality takes place. Once fully deployed, you can access miner resources through a validator to reserve docker containers. If your stack can run on docker, then it can run on SN27. As for actually allocating miner resources, the Neural Internet validator is building out a platform to rent the compute power from miners through their validator’s access to these resources.

 You have 20 challenges to solve:

Can I move my miner from one server to another without having to stop it? If yes then ho do i go about doing so?
True story: tried it with 18 x 4090 and got turbo rekt
is that "on"?

- Set up the new server.
- Install nginx on the old server.
- Create a server block in nginx that will listen on the old miner's port and proxy_pass to the new server:port.
- Start the new miner, wait for it to be listening.
- Stop the old miner, restart nginx with your proxy in place.
- Wait for requests to stop coming in to old miner (tail -f /var/log/nginx/access.log), then stop nginx.
If done properly, zero missed requests.
